reviews.review: How do you possibly end a 9 episode epic adventure that pleases everyone in 2.5 hours? You cant!  But this film answers questions, brings excitement, nostalgia, and an epic soundtrack to fans of a life-defining saga. It was everything I wanted and hoped for!  I didnt want new and innovative I wanted the look and feel that made me feel something, and this delivered!  The last 45 minutes (and last 5 minutes) left me with goosebumps and left me feeling completely satisfied about the way J.J. Abrams chose to finish this story. I wondered what the film title meant for months, and Im happy that I now know and that all of my guesses werent anything close!  A fitting finale. Dont be deterred by the negative if youre a fan of the series.
Perfect ending to the saga and trilogy! Love the way they honored Leia, the most BA Disney Princess. Can't wait to see it again.
I thought ROS was excellent, a finale that nobody could possibly perfect.  Enjoyed, and will see again.
I actually loved the movie, it was very exciting to watch .
Thoroughly enjoyed it. Wrapped it up perfectly.
This movie was filled with action pack scenes and great emotional moments that remind us why we love Star Wars.

It was as satisfying a finish as possible for such a long running story.  It had a great balance of fan service, new ideas, action and humor. It righted the ship from Last Jedi, which I thought was ok but not the direction the story should've went.  I find it hilarious that the critics are putting this one down for pretty much the same reasons they hailed Force Awakens, but that's critics for you.

I really enjoyed this movie! I find that when it comes to Star Wars movies what I enjoy (TLJ) the majority of others do not. I'm a huge Star Wars fan and do not have hate for any of the movies. I would say this one is the best of the trilogy.

This was a fun but messy movie more focused on appeasing the fans the telling a good story, to the extent that the movie feels more like a checklist of items to check of rather then a cohesive plot with any purpose in itself beyond finishing the trilogy making those mad at last jedi happy along the way. It was fun and had neat spectacles but was a mess and sometimes right out uninteresting.
Excellent finale. Not sure what happened with the paid critics. The fan score speaks for itself.
